---
import {getCollection} from 'astro:content'; import BaseLayout from '../../app/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'; import PostGrid from '../../widgets/blog-preview/PostGrid.astro';
const posts=(await getCollection('blog')).sort((a,b)=>b.data.pubDate.valueOf()-a.data.pubDate.valueOf()); const title='Image Resizing and Compression Guides | Image Resizer'; const description='Practical guides to image resizing, compression, file formats, social dimensions, and private browser-based image processing.';
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description} pageClass="blog-page"><section class="blog-hero"><div><span class="eyebrow">Field notes</span><h1>Better images, fewer guesses</h1></div><div><p>Practical guides for choosing dimensions, controlling file size, and understanding what image compression changes.</p><a class="rss" href="/blog/rss.xml">Follow the blog via RSS</a></div></section><PostGrid {posts}/><section class="section prose"><h2>About these image guides</h2><p>Every guide focuses on a decision that appears during ordinary image resizing. Some explain common dimensions, while others look at compression, privacy, and the differences between JPEG, PNG, and WebP.</p><p>The examples support the private image resizer available on this site. Articles are written for people who need a dependable result, not a collection of repeated search phrases.</p></section></BaseLayout>
<style>.blog-hero{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.2fr .8fr;gap:4rem;align-items:end;margin:4rem 0}.blog-hero p{color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:1.08rem}.rss{display:inline-flex;margin-top:1rem;color:var(--blue);font-weight:800;text-decoration:none}@media(max-width:700px){.blog-hero{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin:2.5rem 0}}</style>
